#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/dynamicrouting_rip.rst:3
msgid "Dynamic Routing: Configuration: RIP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/dynamicrouting_rip.rst:6
msgid ""
"RIP should not be used in larger networks due to the limited hop count. "
"Cosider using OSPF in such cases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/dynamicrouting_rip.rst:9
msgid ""
"Saving the settings will apply them and reload the daemon. This means you"
" may lose the connection to your firewall for some seconds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/dynamicrouting_rip.rst:11
msgid ""
"RIP is a well known distance vector protocol. It may be preferred to be "
"used in smaller networks, where the topology is not too complex and the "
"possibillity of loops is small."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/dynamicrouting_rip.rst:18
msgid "Enable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/dynamicrouting_rip.rst:20
msgid ""
"enables the routing protocol if the support of routing protocols is "
"enabled in general. If you check this box, RIP will be enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/dynamicrouting_rip.rst:23
msgid "Version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/dynamicrouting_rip.rst:25
msgid ""
"Enter 1 or 2 here. 1 is “classful” which means, that this routing "
"protocol does not support variable length routing. If you choose version "
"2, variable length subnet masks are supported. In most cases, you want to"
" choose version 2 here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/dynamicrouting_rip.rst:29
msgid "Passive Interfaces"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/dynamicrouting_rip.rst:31
msgid ""
"Interfaces, which are known by the routing daemon, but no updates are "
"sent. You should add interfaces with networks here, which do not have any"
" other routers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/dynamicrouting_rip.rst:35
msgid "Route Redistribution"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/dynamicrouting_rip.rst:37
msgid "Also send routes from other sources to neighbors (if desired)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/dynamicrouting_rip.rst:40
msgid "Networks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/dynamicrouting_rip.rst:42
msgid ""
"Add the networks here which should be known by the router and which are "
"subject to be sent to the neighbors. Passive interfaces will not be used "
"to look for another router."
msgstr ""

